>Description:
Can we get keyboard shortcuts for Show/Hide Definitions and Interactions?  I know we have C-d and C-e, which are awesome, except they don't work once you turn off keybindings, which any power user is liable to do.  The current interaction pattern of Alt <pause> V <pause> I is pretty clunky, at least on Windows, and on a laptop screen I end up having to type it *all the time*.  

I believe there are several unused F keys -- how about F2/F3, or some other keys that are on the main part of the keyboard?  They can even replace C-d/C-e.
